cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on image synthesis, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed algorithm involves generating images through a pyramidal approach, which involves upscaling and refining the estimated image several times. This approach is based on machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also fall under the subcategories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the generation performance, which could be relevant to the subfield of graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
